# WHAT IT IS
#   social-cli is Letta's "agent-optimized social media CLI"
#   — a single command-line surface that an AI agent can drive
#   to read from, post to, and interact with both Bluesky (via
#   the AT Protocol) and X / Twitter (via twitter-api-v2).
#   The contract is:  YAML in, YAML out, exit codes for agents.
#
#   Every command writes typed YAML artifacts that the agent's
#   memory layer can ingest verbatim:
#     • `social-cli sync` → fetches notifications from all
#       configured platforms, dedupes against per-platform
#       cursor state, and writes them into the agent's state
#       directory as `inbox-<platform>.yaml` (Bluesky →
#       `inbox-bsky.yaml`, X → `inbox-x.yaml`, etc.)
#     • `social-cli dispatch` → reads typed posts out of
#       `outbox-<platform>.yaml` and publishes them
#     • `social-cli feed` → fetches a timeline / custom feed
#       and writes it to `feed.yaml` for the agent to read
#     • `social-cli check` → returns exit 0 if inbox has
#       actionable items, exit 1 if empty
#     • `social-cli rate-limits` → typed rate-limit snapshot
#       per platform
#     • `social-cli doctor` → environment / state hygiene
#       inspector
#
#   Bluesky-specific surface includes:  Margin Notes 2.0 via
#   the `annotate` / `bookmark` / `highlight` commands (W3C
#   Annotation Model), Semble PDS integration (`semble`,
#   `add-card`, `connect`), and the `repost-media` extractor
#   that lifts media from any existing post.
#
#   X-specific surface includes:  the twitter-api-v2 driver
#   for `post` / `reply` / `thread` / `like` / `delete` /
#   `follow` / `block` against the same unified verb set.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.ts commander.js
#                       chain — 30 unique `.command(...)`
#                       entries; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       letta-ai/social-cli/contents/src/
#                       cli.ts`)
#
#   social-cli <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Ingest + dispatch:
#     sync [OPTIONS]                 Fetch notifications →
#                                    stateDir/inbox-<platform>.
#                                    yaml
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORMS...>  Platforms to sync
#                                      [default: all]
#       --unread-only                  Only fetch unread
#                                      [default: true]
#       -n, --limit <N>                Max per platform
#                                      [default: 50]
#       -o, --output <FILE>            Legacy shared output
#                                      file  [default:
#                                      inbox.yaml]
#       --max-items <N>                Max inbox items before
#                                      truncating  [default:
#                                      200]
#       --users-dir <PATH>             User memory dir
#       --auto-create-users            Create missing user
#                                      memory files during sync
#       --reset                        Clear cursors and
#                                      re-fetch all
#       --clear                        Clear cursors AND local
#                                      inbox
#       --media                        Download attached media
#       --attachments-dir <PATH>       Override attachments
#                                      root  [default:
#                                      ./attachments]
#
#     dispatch [FILE]                Dispatch posts from
#                                    platform-specific outbox
#                                    YAML files
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      Platform to dispatch
#                                      from (bsky, x)
#       --dry-run                      Validate only, do not
#                                      post
#
#   Health + status:
#     doctor [--migrate]             Check runtime state and
#                                    local hygiene
#       --migrate                      Move legacy root-level
#                                      runtime files into the
#                                      state directory
#     check [-t <N>] [-p <PLATFORM>] Check if inbox has
#                                    actionable items
#       -t, --threshold <N>            Minimum items to
#                                      trigger  [default: 1]
#     rate-limits [-p PLATFORMS...]  Show rate limit status
#     whoami [-p PLATFORMS...]       Show current account info
#
#   Reading:
#     search <QUERY> [OPTIONS]       Search posts on a platform
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       -n, --limit <N>                [default: 10]
#     feed [OPTIONS]                 Fetch timeline → feed.yaml
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       -n, --limit <N>                [default: 50]
#       -o, --output <FILE>            [default: feed.yaml]
#       --feed <AT-URI>                Feed generator AT-URI
#                                      (custom feeds)
#     posts <HANDLE> [-p PLATFORM]   Fetch recent posts by a
#                                    user
#     profile <HANDLE>               Get a user profile (read)
#     get <URI>                      Get a specific post by
#                                    AT-URI
#
#   Writing:
#     post <TEXT> [OPTIONS]          Post to a platform
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       --quote <ID>                   Quote / repost a post
#       --reply-to <ID>                Post as a reply
#       -m, --media <PATHS...>         Media files to attach
#     reply <TEXT> [OPTIONS]         Reply to a post
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       -m, --media <PATHS...>
#     thread <POSTS...> [OPTIONS]    Post a thread (each
#                                    positional arg is one
#                                    post)
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       -m, --media <PATHS...>         Media for first post
#     update-profile [OPTIONS]       Update profile
#     create [OPTIONS]               Create a record
#     delete <ID>                    Delete a post by ID / URI
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#     like <ID>                      Like a post by ID / URI
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#
#   Margin Notes 2.0  (Bluesky-only, via the W3C Annotation
#                       Model on at.margin.note records):
#     annotate [TEXT] [OPTIONS]      Annotate a URL or post
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       --motivation <TYPE>            W3C motivation
#                                      [default: commenting]
#       --quote <TEXT>                 Exact text to anchor to
#     bookmark [OPTIONS]             Bookmark a post (alias
#                                    for `annotate --
#                                    motivation: bookmarking`)
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       -t, --text <TEXT>              Optional note
#     highlight [OPTIONS]            Highlight text in a post
#       -p, --platform <PLATFORM>      [default: bsky]
#       -t, --text <TEXT>              Optional note
#     repost-media <URI> [-t TEXT]   Repost media from an
#                                    existing Bluesky post
#
#   Social graph:
#     follow <HANDLE> [-p PLATFORM]  Follow an account
#     block <HANDLE> [-p PLATFORM]   Block an account
#     list [-p PLATFORM]             List your social lists
#
#   Semble PDS integration  (Bluesky-only):
#     semble                         Semble PDS account ops
#     add-card                       Add a card to a Semble
#                                    profile
#     connect                        Connect to a Semble PDS
#                                    instance
#
#   Blog publishing:
#     blog [OPTIONS]                 Cross-publish a blog post
#     publish [OPTIONS]              Publish queued blog posts
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
